The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bangla make a solid start
                                                   Bangla make a solid start
                      
	Basseterre: Bangladesh bowled out West Indies for 248 in the third and final one-day International Friday, with only opener Andre Fletchers 52 off 42 balls boosting the hosts total.               
	At midnight, Bangladesh were 83 for one in 15 overs. Junaid Siddique (32) and Mohammed Ashraful (19) were at the crease               
	Fletcher smashed eight boundaries and three sixes at Warner Park as he seeks to help his team avoid a 3-0 series sweep.         
	West Indies received useful contributions from Darren Sammy (40 off 33 balls), captain Floyd Reifer (40) and Travis Dowlin (38), but the innings ended after 47.4 overs.         
	There were two wickets apiece for Mahmudullah (2/38), Mahbubul Alam (2/42) and Abdur Razzak (2/63).           (AP)                                                                                                                   
